A vast translucent balloon floating in an infinite cosmos, its iridescent membrane showing countless tiny human silhouettes pressed against the inside surface, gazing outward. Beyond the balloon's skin lies pure luminous void—not darkness but radiant emptiness, soft gradients of pearl and mist. Inside the balloon, fragmented images of lightning bolts, stars, and natural phenomena drift like memories, each rendered in different historical artistic styles from cave paintings to scientific diagrams. The balloon itself hovers above an endless still ocean that reflects nothing, its surface perfectly mirror-like yet showing only subtle ripples. Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor washes, dreamy atmospheric perspective, delicate linework, and that signature ethereal quality of light filtering through translucent surfaces, gentle color palette of soft blues, whites, and subtle warm accents.
